<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-28T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-28T21:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3926: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-29T10:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 29,
                                        1921—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 29—6:49
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>235. Following from Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“June 27, noon. The Government reports capture of Wuchow, details
                                    are not available. Kwangtung troops steadily gaining ground in
                                    the west, elsewhere doubtful, Americans at Wuchow brought to
                                    Hongkong by the British gunboat <hi rend="italic">Tarantula</hi>.”</p></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ruddock</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>